The Zamfara state House of Assembly has voted for the impeachment of the state Deputy Governor Barrister Mahdi Aliyu Gusau. At Wednesday’s plenary, 20 out 24 members voted for the impeachment of the Deputy Governor after the report submitted by the judicial panel of investigation found him guilty of the allegations levelled against him. The report was read by the Speaker of the Assembly Honorable Nasiru Muazu Magarya. More subsequently…